
<h1>Job Queue Manager</h1>

<section style="display:grid;align-content:start;gap:1rem">

	{{ cms.form.jobqueueStats() }}

	<p>This will clear the all the pending import jobs for <em><u>every collection</u></em>.
	This will not delete any items that have already been imported.</p>

	{{ cms.form.clearqueue({
		label      : 'Clear Import Queue',
	}) }}

	<section style="margin-top:3rem;padding-left:0" class="doc-content">
		<h4 style="">Process Jobs Scheduled Job</h4>

		<p>The following command should be the exact command that you will need to in order to process the job
		queue in the background.</p>
		<p><em>If there is no path to the PHP command, you may need to find out what that is
		from your hosting company. Depending on your server, it may or may not need it.</em></p>

		<pre><code>{{ cms.processJobQueueCommand() }}</code></pre>
	</section>

	{{ cms.jobQueuePendingInfo() }}
	{{ cms.jobQueueFailedInfo() }}

</section>

<style>
.jobqueue-table-wrapper {
	max-height: 400px;
	overflow-y: auto;
	border: 1px solid #ddd;
	border-radius: 4px;
}

.jobqueue-preview {
	width: 100%;
	font-size: 0.9em;
	border-collapse: collapse;
}

.jobqueue-preview thead {
	position: sticky;
	top: 0;
	background: var(--color-bg, #fff);
	z-index: 10;
}

.jobqueue-preview th,
.jobqueue-preview td {
	padding: 0.5rem;
	text-align: left;
	border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
}

.jobqueue-preview th {
	font-weight: 600;
	border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
}

.jobqueue-preview.pending-jobs tbody tr:hover {
	background-color: rgba(0, 150, 0, 0.05);
}

.jobqueue-preview.failed-jobs tbody tr:hover {
	background-color: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.05);
}

.jobqueue-preview-section {
	margin-top: 2rem;
}

.jobqueue-preview-section:first-of-type {
	margin-top: 3rem;
}

.jobqueue-preview-section h3 {
	margin-top: 0;
	margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
</style>

